If DMP or SMP is specified, DMP/SMP is used and dmp/smp values defined in the Nastran command line ignored during Actran call and still use for Nastran sequences. It is possible to launch Nastran DMP=1 SMP=8 and have internally Actran running DMP=4 SMP=4. Of course, the user should make sure that the underlying resources are compatible with the two dmp/smp requests. The value of MEM will be divided by DMP, if any or value of DMP. By default, Actran get what master node has which is HICORE. MEM can only be adjusted upward, not downward. If MEM is more than HICORE, Actran get MEM. Otherwise, Actran get HICORE. 3.In the frame of Workflow Manager (Space and Virtual SEA), the Actran allocated memory is got from workflow manager job submittal memory. If MEM is specified, it will thus be ignored. 4.SPM allows to choose the precision of the matrix to be assembled (double by default SPM=0). SPM=1 allows a resources request reduction (both memory and disk) and consequently a potential reduction of the computation time. On the other hand, results precisions might be deteriorated in some cases where the matrix conditioning is worse so that results are more sensible to solver precision. 5.BLR allows to activate Block Low-Rank (BLR) approximation for the factorization and back transformation steps. Two values are possible, 0 or 1: a.0 implies full rank factorization (no BLR approximation). b.1 activates BLR approximation with an automatic choice of BLR options by the solver. 6.BLRTOL defines the dropping parameter which will impact the accuracy of the solution. Using smaller value will enhance the accuracy but it will slightly increase the computational time and the required memory.SOLVAC 8 4 2.9 1 Describer Meaning SMP Number of processors used for Shared Memory Parallel for Actran.     MSC Nastran Quick Reference Guide The NLPERF - High Performance Nonlinear Solver3072 M ain Index The NLPERF - High Performance Nonlinear Solver The NLPERF solver (High-Performance Nonlinear Solver), first introduced in the MSC Nastran 2024.1 release, is a high-performance nonlinear solver based on a revamped SOL400 architecture. The supported and unsupported input entries for this solver are described in this section.
    Note the following general rule: •NLMOPTS,NLSSEL is used to activate NLPERF. Default is the classic solver (CNLS). For more details, refer to the NLMOPTS entry. •When NLMOPTS,NLSSEL,NLPERF is used, a FATAL is issued when unsupported input entries are encountered. •When NLMOPTS,NLSSEL,AUTO is used, a WARNING is issued when unsupported input entries are encountered and the analysis switches to CNLS. Executing MSC Nastran MSC Nastran is executed from the command line using the command nast_ver (where nast_ver=nast20241 ). This command sets environment variables in order for MSC Nastran to correctly execute on your system and it also has capabilities to predict memory and solvers (as of MSC Nastran 2022.3 with solve=auto ). In NLPERF, an additional command line option allows users to access the Convergence Monitor to check convergence behaviour. There are two ways to access the Convergence Monitor for checking analysis status: Activating the Convergence Monitor via the Command Line The Convergence Monitor may be activated at the beginning of the analysis by requesting MONITOR in the command line, for example, nast_ver input_data_file monitor=yes keywordsThe default for MONITOR is NO, i.e., the GUI monitor won’t be activated when starting to run Nastran analysis. Activating by MSC utility The Convergence Monitor may be activated at any time through a MSC standalone utility as follows: msc_v er monitor job.itr The GUI monitor scans the file JOB.ITR and provides the necessary convergence information on the screen.

    The relationship between dependent and independent degrees-of-freedom for rigid elements and MPCs may be altered from the user’s input specification via PARAM,AUTOMSET,YES or PARAM, AUTOMSET,LUSOL. For PARAM, AUTOMSET,YES, or PARAM,AUTOMSET, LUSOL, dependent degrees-of-freedom of the model, the M-set are automatically determined by employing a rectangular decomposition of the RMG matrix. Note that in NLPERF AUTOMSET is applied to rigid element constraints only. EPSILONT Default = SECANT This parameter only applies to SOLs 106 and 400 ANALYSIS=NLSTAT, and only applies to CQUAD4, CTRIA3, CQUADR, and CTRIAR elements that are not associated with the enhanced nonlinear materials (PSHLN1). FOLLOWK
    Default = YES In SOLs 101,103, 105, 106, 107, 108, 109, 110, 111, 112, 115, 116, and 400, FOLLOWK=YES (Default) requests the inclusion of follower force stiffness in the differential stiffness. FOLLOWK=NO requests that the follower force stiffness not to be included. For FOLLOWK=YES in SOLs 101,103, 105, 107, 108, 109, 110, 111, 112, 115, and 116, a separate static subcase is required and the STATSUB command is also required in the eigenvalue subcase. In nonlinear analysis (SOL 106 and 400), the follower force is included if PARAM,LGDISP,1 is specified. FOLLOWK is ignored in SOL 106 and SOL 400 if LGDISP is not specified. KDIAG Default = -1.0 (SOLs 106, 153, and SOL 400 with non-contact analysis), or 0.0 (SOL 400 with contact analysis) In SOLs 106 (nonlinear static analysis), 153 (steady state heat transfer), and SOL 400 (nonlinear static and transient analysis), KDIAG may be used to eliminate spurious mechanisms and singularities in the nonlinear stiffness matrix. K6ROT Default = 100.     MSC Nastran Quick Reference Guide Parameter Entries3082 Main Index LGDISP LGDISP is a global parameter. For the case with multiple LGDISP definitions, Nastran will use the first definition for all the subcases and steps. Default = -1 NLAYERS Default = 5 for CQUAD4 and CTRIA, 7 for CQUADR and CTRIAR, 3 for CAXISYM (minimum=1, maximum=12) (SOLs 106, 129, 153, 159, and 400) NLAYERS is used in material nonlinear analysis only and is the number of layers used to integrate through the thickness of CQUAD4, CTRlA3 CQUADR, CTRIAR and CAXISYM elements with isotropic material properties. Set NLAYERS=1 for efficiency if no bending is selected (MID2=0 or -1 on all PSHELL entries). Do not specify NLAYERS=1 if MID2 is greater than zero. A larger value of NLAYERS will give greater accuracy at the cost of computing time and storage requirements. For CQUADR and CTRIAR, the maximum is 11. WTMASS Default = 1.0 The terms of the structural mass matrix are multiplied by the value of WTMASS when they are generated. In coupled fluid-structure analysis WTMASS is applied to the structural portion of the model only. WTMASS applies to MFLUID entries but it is not recommended for use in hydroelastic problems
